race.comment: TENNESSEE WHISKEY (3) has placed two from two around this circuit and has been racing very consistently of late. Drawn to get a gun run in transit from the inside alley and looks the one they all have to run down. OUR ORATOR (2) has placed over this staying trip and will be cherry-ripe for this 2400m contest. A big run would not surprise. MAN TALK (5) shed the maiden tag in impressive fashion last time out and is sure to have derived a stack of confidence from that victory. Can go right on with the job now. GIDDY GAN'S JOY (6) goes well for hoop Taylor who has a win and two placings from just four steers. In the mix on best form. THE CLAIMANT (4) gets in light with the 3kg claim and may earn a cheque.
